result.execSummary:
The defendant Cardis Cardell Willis was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Incident], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Original Transcript (22 pages) commencing 05/13/2014 SENTENCING HEARING received and filed.
COURT ORDERED 45 DAYS CONDITION BE IMPOSED AND STAYED TO BE USED AT THE DISCRETION OF THE PROBATION AGENT.  Days were imposed at sentencing but not entered on CCAP.

Defendant Cardis Cardell Willis in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Sarra M. Kiaie appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
  Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is compliant or mostly compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is not needed.

Defendant Cardis Cardell Willis in court with attorney Anne M Jaspers.  Defendant Cardis Cardell Willis in custody.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  
AS TO COUNT 1:  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction, concurrent with Counts 3 and 4 with credit for 99 days time served.  
.
AS TO COUNT 3:  Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 39 MONTHS in the Wisconsin State Prison, consecutive to any other sentence; credit for 99 days served.  Court ordered 15 MONTHS Initial Term Of Confinement and 24 MONTHS Extended Supervision.
Court found defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration or Earned Release Programs.
.
AS TO COUNT 4:  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction, concurrent with Counts 1 and 3 with credit for 99 days time served. 
.
COURT STAYED THE SENTENCES and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 2 YEARS.

Conditions of Probation:
- No further violations of the law.
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety; random urine screens.
- Attend treatment and/or counseling as determined.
- No contact with victim unless approved by agent.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay all costs, surcharges and supervision fees.
 
Received and filed: Pretrial Sentence Credit, Notice of Right to Seek Post-Conviction Relief, Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence. 
.
Court advised defendant of penalties for violating the no contact order and due to this DV conviction s/he may never possess firearms or ammunition.
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon s/he must provide a DNA sample, pay the surcharge, his/her voting rights are suspended and s/he may never possess firearms.  The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for August 22, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
Sentencing hearing scheduled for 05-13-2014 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Cardis Cardell Willis in court with attorney Anne M Jaspers.  Defendant Cardis Cardell Willis in custody.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court orders Count 1 AMENDED as follows:
Misdemeanor Battery, contrary to Wisconsin State Stats. 940.19(1).

As to Counts 1, 3 and 4:
Repeater penalty enhancer is dismissed.

As to Count 1, 3 and 4:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY to the amended charge.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the Defendant guilty of the amended charges and enters judgment of conviction into the record forthwith. 

As to Count 2:
Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders Count 2 DISMISSED but read-in as to sentencing.

Jury trial is vacated.

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department pending sentencing.  No PSI ordered.
Court orders case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 40.
